<figureCitation box="[451,535,844,868]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1786,1809]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,823,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,801,1765]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Microphilypnus acangaquara sp. nov. a) MZUSP 108204, holotype, Brazil: Pará, rio Tapajós basin, São Luís 15.1 mm SL. b) MZUSP 27015, paratype, same data as the holotype, 14.1 mm SL. c) MCP 15317, paratype, Brazil: Pará, rio Tapajós basin, rio Itapacurá, 16.8 mm SL. Photographs by R. A. Caires (a, b) and André da Silva Casas (c)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201754/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[503,535,844,868]" pageId="15" pageNumber="54" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
): ground color yellowish, with chromatophores on posterior margin of the scales forming three irregular series of spots along the flanks; row of slender dark brown markings along belly, a vertical row of small dark spots from hind border of eye to chin and other from anterior margin of eye to upper jaw; small black dots on opercle; fins with inconspicuous series of dark brown spots along the rays; eyeball black or silvery on lower half and dark on the upper one; iris black.
</paragraph>
